{
  "texts": [
    "Responses to the question of whether an AI system is genuinely intelligent in relation to the knowledge it possesses have taken two distinct paths.",
    "The affirmative stance suggests that systems equipped with knowledge indeed exhibit intelligence.",
    "This category encompasses knowledge systems, expert systems, and all knowledge-based models leveraging a knowledge base to address variously complex problems.",
    "Additionally, it includes systems whose semantic knowledge relies on syntactic structures.",
    "This perspective contrasts with the view that regards such knowledge as fake knowledge inasmuch merely symbolic manipulation, devoid of genuine semantic content."
  ]
}